OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 13 Jun to Mon 22 Jun
OL,6,FThe start of this period will see a
OL,7,Ftransition to a generally more settled
OL,8,Fweather pattern for much of the UK, as
OL,9,Fhigh pressure exerts more an
OL,10,Finfluence. This will be most
OL,11,Fnoticeable across southern and eastern
OL,12,Fparts, whereas areas further northwest
OL,13,Fcould often be cloudier with some rain
OL,14,Fat times. With the build of pressure
OL,15,Fwill come an increase in temperatures,
OL,16,Fwith the potential for very warm or
OL,17,Fhot conditions to become established
OL,18,Fby mid-month, especially across parts
OL,19,Fof England and Wales. High pressure is
OL,20,Ffavoured to remain close by to the UK
OL,21,Ftowards the end of this period,
OL,22,Fbringing widely settled conditions and
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Foften above average temperatures.
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1780927878
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 23 Jun to Tue 7 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure is likely to be close by
OL,7,Fto the UK at the start of this period,
OL,8,Falthough its position relatively to
OL,9,Fthe UK is more uncertain. Whilst
OL,10,Fsettled conditions look most likely,
OL,11,Fwith a lot of dry weather in the
OL,12,Foffing, temperatures are more
OL,13,Funcertain, though the potential does
OL,14,Fexist for further hot spells,
OL,15,Fespecially in the south. Into July, it
OL,16,Fis possible that pressure may lower
OL,17,Ffrom the south increasing the chance
OL,18,Fof thunderstorms here.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
